[assistant] Implemented a new URL Fetch coverage test in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/com.google.appengine/appengine-api-1.0-sdk/2.0.32/src/test/java/com_google_appengine/appengine_api_1_0_sdk/Appengine_api_1_0_sdkTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Current existing coverage in the file already exercised:
[assistant] - Datastore entities, keys, queries, projections, and fetch options
[assistant] - Search documents, fields, facets, refinements, and sort/query options
[assistant] - Blobstore value objects, image creation, and mail message value objects
[assistant] - Task queue options and memcache serialization
[assistant] - Users service environment-backed identity
[assistant] - ApiProxy-backed mail, capabilities, and task queue request marshalling
[assistant] 
[assistant] New feature added:
[assistant] - URL Fetch service request/response flow via the public URL Fetch API.
[assistant] 
[assistant] The new test covers:
[assistant] - `URLFetchServiceFactory.getURLFetchService()`
[assistant] - `HTTPRequest`, `HTTPMethod`, `HTTPHeader`, URL fetch `FetchOptions`
[assistant] - POST payload marshalling
[assistant] - Redirect and certificate validation options
[assistant] - Request protobuf sent through `ApiProxy`
[assistant] - `HTTPResponse` status, content, final URL, uncombined headers, and combined repeated headers
[assistant] 
[assistant] I also extended the existing in-file `RecordingDelegate` only for the new `urlfetch.Fetch` call so the test remains self-contained and native-image compatible.
[assistant] 
[assistant] No reachability metadata or build files were changed. Tests were not run, per instruction.
